               int[] selectedValues,

               boolean printOut,
               double lambda,
               int distanceFunction,
               double normalClusterThreshold,
               java.lang.String name)
        The constructor creates new Profile object from given parameters.
        Parameters:
        minMaxValues - HashMap<String,int[]> that presents minimum and maximum values for the given features that are used for normalization.
        selectedValues - int[] array that presents the indexes of selected features to be used for profile building.
        maxChildren - int value that presents maximum number of child nodes inside a single CFTreeNode.
        threshold - double value that presents the threshold that defines the maximum allowed radius of a single leaf CFTreeNode.
        pointLength - int value value that presents the length of the input data points.
        delta - double value that presents the maximum delta value for the ADWIN windows.
        clearThreshold - double value that presents the percentage for the calculation of the minimum allowed size of the cluster.
        checkStep - int value that presents the number of iterations before we check for anomaly.
        maxBins - int value that presents the maximum number of bins the exponential histogram can have.
        sizeOfBin - int value that presents the maximum number of values inside of a single bin.
        thresholdT - double value that presents the maximum allowed time difference.
        timestampRateMax - double value that presents the maximum difference between two updates to the cluster.
        formats - DateTimeFormatter[] array that presents the possible formats for parsing DateTime.
        printOut - boolean value that enables printing of additional data to results.
